@startuml TestingLayer3InfraIntegration
' SPEC source: internal/egress/integration_test.go
' Layer 3 — live egress topology with real containers, NO model.
' Build tag: //go:build integration — not compiled by default go test ./...
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

title Layer 3 · Infra integration — real containers, no model\n(-tags=integration + PROVEO_EGRESS_INTEGRATION=1)

actor "integration test\n(BuildPlan + ExecRunner)\n//go:build integration" as Test <<actor>>

package "per-session egress topology (Docker)" as Topo {
 component "curl agent probe\ncurlimages/curl (no agent, no keys)" as Probe <<container>>
 component "agent-net\n--internal" as ANet <<queue>>
 component "proveo-egress\nTLS intercept + record" as Proxy <<container>>
 component "enforce-net\n--internal" as ENet <<queue>>
 component "squid:3128\nenforcement + write-pin" as Squid <<container>>
 component "egress-net\ninternet-capable" as XNet <<queue>>
 component "flows.ndjson\n(decrypted, no query string)" as Flows <<storage>>
 component "broker.env\n(host .env → inject)" as BrokerFile <<storage>>
}

cloud "internet (example.com)" as Net <<external>>

Test --> Topo : stage squid config + Apply plan
Test --> BrokerFile : writeBrokerEnv from host .env\n(CURSOR_API_KEY regression)
Probe --> ANet : HTTP_PROXY + trusts CA
ANet --> Proxy
Proxy --> Flows : record
Proxy --> ENet
ENet --> Squid
Squid --> XNet
XNet --> Net : allowed reads
BrokerFile ..> Proxy : mount /broker:ro

note bottom of Topo
Asserts the load-bearing invariants: HTTPS GET succeeds through
agent->proxy->squid->internet with the generated **CA trusted**; the decrypted
request is recorded to **flows.ndjson**; a proxy-bypassing request **fails**
(the --internal agent net has no direct egress). Broker-aware case: host .env
key → broker.env mounted; agent plan carries sentinel. Teardown via **t.Cleanup**.
Wait for CA file / HTTP ready — never fixed sleep-only sync.
Deterministic, keyless — no model is involved.
end note

note right of Test
Practices from Testcontainers (without the library): wait strategies,
t.Cleanup, env gate + docker LookPath skip. Orchestration stays BuildPlan
(no testcontainers-go — would duplicate owned topology).
Credential inject/strip proven in-process (egressproxy); this layer proves
network topology + broker mount wiring.
end note
@enduml
